cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SD

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as language modeling and code-switching. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a deep generative model for text synthesis. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of deep learning techniques for language modeling. The paper also introduces a novel architecture, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves experiments and evaluation, which could place it under cs.SD (Software Engineering).
